#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/pgcrypto.xml:845(para)
msgid "For more details see <literal>man gpg</literal>, <ulink url=\"http://www.gnupg.org/gph/en/manual.html\">The GNU Privacy Handbook</ulink> and other documentation on <ulink url=\"http://www.gnupg.org\"/>."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/pgcrypto.xml:854(title)
msgid "Limitations of PGP code"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/pgcrypto.xml:858(para)
msgid "No support for signing. That also means that it is not checked whether the encryption subkey belongs to the master key."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/pgcrypto.xml:864(para)
msgid "No support for encryption key as master key. As such practice is generally discouraged, this should not be a problem."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/pgcrypto.xml:870(para)
msgid "No support for several subkeys. This may seem like a problem, as this is common practice. On the other hand, you should not use your regular GPG/PGP keys with <filename>pgcrypto</filename>, but create new ones, as the usage scenario is rather different."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/pgcrypto.xml:882(title)
msgid "Raw encryption functions"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/pgcrypto.xml:884(para)
msgid "These functions only run a cipher over data; they don't have any advanced features of PGP encryption. Therefore they have some major problems:"
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/pgcrypto.xml:890(para)
msgid "They use user key directly as cipher key."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/pgcrypto.xml:895(para)
msgid "They don't provide any integrity checking, to see if the encrypted data was modified."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/pgcrypto.xml:901(para)
msgid "They expect that users manage all encryption parameters themselves, even IV."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/pgcrypto.xml:907(para)
msgid "They don't handle text."
msgstr ""

#: /home/carloratm/progetti/postgresql-source/doc-9.0.4/pgcrypto.xml:912(para)
msgid "So, with the introduction of PGP encryption, usage of raw encryption functions is discouraged."
msgstr ""

